element.name: Waterbridge by Eternal Treasure Seekers. , Traditional Cache (1.5/3)
element.description: A nice cache near the Leinster Aquaduct
element.long-description:
The Leinster Aquaduct is the crossing point of the Grand Canal over the river Liffey. Built in 1783 by Richard Evans this architectural feat is a tribute the skill of 18th century workmen.
This is a small cache wrapped in black fabric. Original contents are a pencil, log, and a few small toys. A slippery slope makes this a little difficult.
